Parliament, Thursday, 26 November 2020 – The Portfolio Committee on Transport will this weekend conduct an oversight at the infamous Moloto Road Development Project. The committee will receive briefings from the South African National Roads Agency Limited and the Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa. The committee will kick-start its visit with a courtesy meeting with the AmaNdebele King, His Majesty Makhosonke II. Details of the visit are as follows: Date: Friday, 27 November 2020 Time: 9h00 Venue: KwaMhlanga (King’s Cluster) ISSUED BY THE PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES. For media enquiries or interviews with the Chairperson, please contact the committee’s Media Officer: Name: Sibongile Maputi (Mr)
